WEBVTT

00:17.166 --> 00:19.916
[footsteps approaching]

00:21.875 --> 00:23.666
[door opens]

00:25.875 --> 00:27.083
[door closes]

00:27.833 --> 00:30.125
[Caitlyn] You really went to the undercity
to get these?

00:30.208 --> 00:31.333
Weren't you afraid?

00:31.416 --> 00:33.416
[Jayce] A little danger is worth the risk,
don't you think?

00:34.166 --> 00:35.125
-Oh.
-[clanking]

00:35.208 --> 00:36.208
[Jayce] Uh, careful.

00:36.291 --> 00:38.166
That's your parents' money
you're dropping.

00:40.000 --> 00:41.625
-[Jayce grunts]
-[door clanking]

00:41.708 --> 00:43.166
[Vi muffled]
Powder, we've gotta go!

00:43.250 --> 00:45.916
-[muffled chatter]
-[Jayce] Hello? Is someone in there?

00:48.875 --> 00:49.791
Hey, open up!

00:50.583 --> 00:52.041
[crackles]

00:53.958 --> 00:55.083
[grunts]

00:56.541 --> 00:57.916
[grumbles]

01:00.291 --> 01:01.791
[cracks]

01:03.708 --> 01:04.666
-[explosion]
-[gasps]

01:08.750 --> 01:09.625
[groans]

01:11.708 --> 01:14.083
[muffled chatter]

01:14.166 --> 01:16.500
[Jayce groans softly]

01:16.583 --> 01:18.041
[hurried footsteps]

01:18.708 --> 01:19.750
[Caitlyn] Jayce?

01:21.833 --> 01:22.833
Jayce!

01:22.916 --> 01:25.416
[wind howls]

01:29.625 --> 01:32.208
[ominous music plays]

01:35.958 --> 01:36.958
[Jayce] Mom!

01:38.208 --> 01:39.916
Mom. Mom, wake up.

01:41.250 --> 01:42.833
[grunts]
Mom.

01:44.375 --> 01:47.958
Help! Please, someone, help us!

01:48.625 --> 01:51.166
Help! Please!

01:57.875 --> 02:01.875
[epic music plays]

02:07.083 --> 02:08.375
[gasps]

02:12.333 --> 02:14.125
No. Wait. Wait.

02:14.875 --> 02:16.791
[chimes]

02:18.916 --> 02:21.000
[whooshing]

02:25.083 --> 02:26.916
[whirring]

02:29.750 --> 02:31.750
[tense music plays]

02:49.208 --> 02:51.416
[birds chirping]

02:54.375 --> 02:55.791
[exhales]

03:01.875 --> 03:03.583
[warbles]

03:09.833 --> 03:12.625
[dramatic music plays]

03:22.875 --> 03:24.291
How?

03:39.500 --> 03:42.333
["Enemy" by Imagine Dragons playing]

03:51.750 --> 03:54.916
♪ I wake up to the sounds
Of the silence that arouse ♪

03:55.000 --> 03:57.958
♪ From my mind to run around
Put my ear up to the ground ♪

03:58.041 --> 04:01.125
♪ I'm searching to behold
The stories that I told ♪

04:01.208 --> 04:03.708
♪ My back is to the world
That was smiling when I turned ♪

04:03.791 --> 04:09.750
♪ Tell you you're the greatest ♪

04:09.833 --> 04:16.125
♪ But once you turn, they hate us ♪

04:17.291 --> 04:19.125
♪ Oh, the misery ♪

04:19.708 --> 04:22.291
♪ Everybody wants to be my enemy ♪

04:23.541 --> 04:26.083
♪ Spare the sympathy ♪

04:26.166 --> 04:29.250
♪ Everybody wants to be my enemy ♪

04:29.333 --> 04:31.458
♪ Hey-o, I swear ♪

04:31.541 --> 04:33.791
♪ I never be insane ♪

04:34.333 --> 04:35.375
♪ My enemy ♪

04:35.458 --> 04:37.416
♪ Hey-o, I swear ♪

04:37.500 --> 04:39.166
♪ I never be insane ♪

04:39.250 --> 04:40.791
♪ Look out for yourself ♪

04:43.166 --> 04:45.583
-[bells tolling]
-[birds chirping]

04:45.666 --> 04:47.500
[Grayson] Let's go over it again.

04:47.583 --> 04:50.291
[Jayce] You have to believe me.
I didn't do this.

04:50.375 --> 04:54.875
Relax, kid. We know it was a break-in
but that doesn't explain this.

04:54.958 --> 04:58.958
There's a lot of restricted items here
and I don't see any permits.

04:59.041 --> 05:00.416
You wanna tell me how you got them?

05:00.500 --> 05:03.291
Hey, hey! Be careful with that, please.

05:03.375 --> 05:06.250
I believe someone
should have said that earlier.

05:07.208 --> 05:08.583
What happened here?

05:10.541 --> 05:11.875
Science, I guess?

05:11.958 --> 05:15.875
Last time I checked,
science didn't require illegal equipment.

05:15.958 --> 05:20.916
Nor was this approved by the Academy.
Who authorized your research?

05:21.000 --> 05:24.208
It was an independent study.
Who are you anyway?

05:24.291 --> 05:26.583
I'm assistant to the Dean of the Academy,

05:26.666 --> 05:29.833
who it may serve you to remember
is also head of the Council.

05:29.916 --> 05:34.750
He sent me here to ensure
that anything dangerous is removed safely.

05:34.833 --> 05:38.291
Which, according to my list, includes you.

05:38.375 --> 05:40.458
What? How am I dangerous?

05:40.541 --> 05:42.833
Uh, that's for the council to decide.

05:47.791 --> 05:51.750
[dog barking in distance]

05:51.833 --> 05:54.625
[footsteps in distance]

05:56.875 --> 05:58.041
[door clanks]

06:01.791 --> 06:04.458
[footsteps approaching]

06:07.291 --> 06:10.083
[mysterious music plays]

06:12.458 --> 06:15.416
Imprisonment. What a curious principle.

06:15.500 --> 06:19.291
We confine the physical body,
yet the mind is still free.

06:19.375 --> 06:21.583
I do love a good conundrum.

06:22.333 --> 06:25.500
I remember the first time
I saw you at the Academy.

06:25.583 --> 06:27.416
You reminded me of myself.

06:27.500 --> 06:32.291
A scientist ready to forge
a new vector of experimentation.

06:33.125 --> 06:35.958
But sometimes we venture too far.

06:36.041 --> 06:39.625
No great science
should ever put lives in danger.

06:40.458 --> 06:43.916
Be honest, now.
What manner of inquiry was this?

06:44.000 --> 06:45.833
Professor Heimerdinger, I…

06:45.916 --> 06:48.833
I believe I've discovered
something truly incredible.

06:48.916 --> 06:51.250
A way to harness magic through science.

06:51.333 --> 06:52.250
Magic?

06:52.333 --> 06:53.333
Yes.

06:53.416 --> 06:54.458
No.

06:54.541 --> 06:55.458
No?

06:55.541 --> 06:57.750
The Arcane is dangerous, Jayce.

06:57.833 --> 07:00.750
A force of nature.
Science cannot control it.

07:01.375 --> 07:03.291
But maybe it can.

07:03.375 --> 07:06.000
I'm close to a breakthrough, I know it.

07:06.083 --> 07:07.750
How old are you, my boy?

07:08.666 --> 07:11.375
-I'm… I'm 24.
-Ah.

07:12.125 --> 07:15.000
Well, I am now 307 years old.

07:15.083 --> 07:19.125
All my life,
I've pursued the mysteries of science,

07:19.208 --> 07:23.166
only to discover
some are better left unsolved.

07:23.250 --> 07:26.333
This, I'm afraid, is one of them.

07:26.416 --> 07:30.375
Own your mistakes before the Council,
admit your work was dangerous,

07:30.458 --> 07:33.208
but speak nothing of magic.

07:34.416 --> 07:36.750
Do that and I theorize you'll get away

07:36.833 --> 07:39.500
with, um, how do you say,
a slap on the wrist.

07:39.583 --> 07:42.250
-[knocks on door]
-[door opens]

07:44.083 --> 07:45.166
[door closes]

07:46.041 --> 07:48.125
[grunting]

07:53.333 --> 07:54.666
[screams]

07:59.208 --> 08:01.000
[grumbles]

08:03.500 --> 08:05.541
Remind me why we bother with this dump.

08:07.541 --> 08:09.166
Vander said to lay low.

08:09.250 --> 08:12.583
Enforcers never come down here,
so this is as good a place as any.

08:12.666 --> 08:16.375
Oh, what's the matter, Mylo?
You worried Powder's gonna beat you again?

08:16.458 --> 08:18.791
Hey, if she didn't keep
fixing these things,

08:18.875 --> 08:19.958
I wouldn't keep missing.

08:22.541 --> 08:25.541
-[powering up]
-[clanking]

08:31.250 --> 08:34.083
You guys know I wouldn't take you
on a job you couldn't handle, right?

08:34.166 --> 08:36.791
Are you kidding?
That was the best job we've ever done.

08:38.291 --> 08:40.291
Maybe just don't take Powder next time.

08:41.083 --> 08:42.041
Um…

08:43.541 --> 08:46.166
[rock music plays]

08:57.166 --> 09:00.208
[indistinct chatter]

09:00.291 --> 09:02.833
[people clamoring]

09:03.416 --> 09:05.625
-Get back.
-[grunts, screams]

09:05.708 --> 09:09.458
-Tell me where I can find them.
-Topsider business ain't my concern.

09:09.541 --> 09:11.916
It's every one
of you trencher's concern now.

09:12.000 --> 09:13.583
Give me a name.

09:18.166 --> 09:19.666
[inhales deeply]

09:21.166 --> 09:23.916
-Hey, guys? You should see this--
-[shatters]

09:31.041 --> 09:33.041
[foreboding music plays]

09:34.958 --> 09:35.916
Search them.

09:38.875 --> 09:41.250
[glass shatters]

09:41.333 --> 09:43.583
Go ahead, idiots. We've got nothing.

09:49.125 --> 09:51.208
[enforcer 1 wheezes]

09:52.333 --> 09:53.208
[gasps]

09:59.458 --> 10:00.958
[shrieks]

10:01.916 --> 10:03.583
[growls, grunts]

10:05.666 --> 10:07.750
Go!
[groans]

10:07.833 --> 10:09.125
[enforcer 1] Go!

10:09.208 --> 10:11.208
[suspenseful music plays]

10:13.541 --> 10:15.916
[breathes heavily]

10:16.000 --> 10:17.333
-[Powder screams]
-[grunts]

10:18.750 --> 10:21.041
-[enforcer 1 screams]
-[Vi] Come on!

10:27.958 --> 10:29.000
[enforcer 1] Get them!

10:31.000 --> 10:32.291
[gasps]

10:33.083 --> 10:35.333
-[enforcer 2 growls]
-[exclaims]

10:37.208 --> 10:38.250
[Ekko whistles]

10:39.416 --> 10:40.333
Over here!

10:40.416 --> 10:41.250
[grunts]

10:43.333 --> 10:44.583
[Powder gasps]

10:47.000 --> 10:48.666
-[Vi grunts]
-[enforcer 2 screams]

10:49.541 --> 10:50.791
[grumbles]

10:51.375 --> 10:54.416
-You need to hide those crystals.
-[Powder] Yeah, no shit.

10:57.083 --> 10:59.000
[Elora]
The House Ferros received your letter.

10:59.083 --> 11:00.708
They insist business is steady.

11:00.791 --> 11:02.500
[Mel] Steady is stagnant, Elora.

11:02.583 --> 11:05.708
[Elora] They wished me to remind you
that it's thanks to their innovations

11:05.791 --> 11:07.708
that you are the richest person
in Piltover.

11:08.291 --> 11:11.041
[sighs]
Yet I remain the poorest Medarda.

11:11.125 --> 11:14.666
Excellent choice, Councilor Medarda.
Supreme challenge.

11:14.750 --> 11:18.833
-If I may…
-We need something revolutionary, Elora.

11:18.916 --> 11:21.791
Something to put Piltover on the map.

11:22.500 --> 11:26.250
-What of today's trial?
-His name is Jayce of House Talis.

11:26.333 --> 11:28.458
A House? Remind me.

11:28.541 --> 11:29.750
They're toolmakers.

11:29.833 --> 11:32.541
I believe they came to renown
for their design of the…

11:32.625 --> 11:35.166
-collapsible pocket wrench.
-[Mel scoffs]

11:35.250 --> 11:38.500
-But Heimerdinger favors him?
-As far as I can tell.

11:38.583 --> 11:39.875
Hmm.

11:40.375 --> 11:41.708
This one.

11:41.791 --> 11:42.875
But that's…

11:42.958 --> 11:45.333
[stutters]
Well, that's a child's toy.

11:45.916 --> 11:47.916
[chuckles]
Good.

11:48.916 --> 11:51.458
[classical music plays]

11:51.541 --> 11:53.291
[Mrs. Kiramman] The boy's got ambition.

11:53.375 --> 11:55.125
It's why we supported him
in the first place.

11:55.208 --> 11:58.000
[Mr. Kiramman] Ambition?
Darling, he nearly blew up our daughter.

11:58.083 --> 12:01.083
[Caitlyn] Jayce had nothing
to do with that. He was robbed.

12:01.166 --> 12:03.666
-We need to help him.
-[Mrs. Kiramman] Caitlyn's right.

12:03.750 --> 12:06.666
We've known Jayce for years.
Besides, we're his patrons.

12:06.750 --> 12:09.791
If anyone is meant
to speak up for him, it's us.

12:10.875 --> 12:14.458
We should hit them back.
We've got the numbers to beat them.

12:14.541 --> 12:16.625
Yeah. Let's teach them
what it means to mess with us.

12:16.708 --> 12:17.916
[all] Yeah!

12:18.000 --> 12:21.291
[crowd shouting in agreement]

12:24.916 --> 12:27.750
-You sure that's what you want?
-[stall holder] Let's do it.

12:28.375 --> 12:32.083
We crossed that bridge once before,
and we all know how that ended.

12:32.166 --> 12:33.875
You're just protecting your kids.

12:35.500 --> 12:40.083
I'm protecting our people.
I'd do the same for any one of you.

12:40.166 --> 12:43.708
We look out for each other.
It's the way it's always been.

12:44.416 --> 12:47.916
This will blow over.
We just need to stand together.

12:48.000 --> 12:51.708
The Vander I knew,
the one who built the underground,

12:51.791 --> 12:53.708
wouldn't be afraid to fight.

12:58.708 --> 13:01.708
-Do I look afraid?
-No.

13:02.208 --> 13:03.833
You look weak.

13:09.041 --> 13:10.666
[Claggor] Why isn't he doing anything?

13:10.750 --> 13:13.333
We kicked the Enforcers' butts
with just the four of us.

13:13.416 --> 13:15.291
Imagine what the whole
of the Lanes could do.

13:15.375 --> 13:19.125
-Jeez, even Powder wants to fight.
-So, why aren't we?

13:20.708 --> 13:22.583
[indistinct chatter]

13:27.750 --> 13:29.125
Spill it, Ekko.

13:29.208 --> 13:30.125
Um…

13:30.208 --> 13:35.833
Oh, okay. Well, um, Vander's got a deal
with the Enforcers.

13:36.416 --> 13:37.500
What deal?

13:38.083 --> 13:40.083
[suspenseful music plays]

13:55.125 --> 13:57.000
For your birthday, Councilor.

13:57.083 --> 14:00.375
Ah, Mel, this is too kind.

14:00.458 --> 14:03.791
[Mel] I'm told it was built only
for the sharpest of minds.

14:03.875 --> 14:06.916
[stammers]
And I bought you some Ginko nuts.

14:07.000 --> 14:09.208
[screams]
Don't you know I'm allergic?

14:09.291 --> 14:10.333
What are you trying to do?

14:10.416 --> 14:11.583
-Kill an old man?
-[door opens]

14:12.833 --> 14:14.583
[suspenseful music playing continues]

14:16.958 --> 14:19.625
[crowd muttering]

14:44.041 --> 14:45.791
[Mrs. Kiramman] Jayce Talis.

14:48.416 --> 14:53.500
You are accused of illegal experimentation
and endangering the citizens of Piltover.

14:54.291 --> 14:56.166
What do you have to say for yourself?

15:00.875 --> 15:04.875
The materials were far more dangerous
than I was aware of,

15:04.958 --> 15:09.583
and I… I now know my actions
were against Academy regulations.

15:09.666 --> 15:14.291
What I did endangered people.
It was reckless, and for that, I'm sorry.

15:14.375 --> 15:19.375
I ask the Council's forgiveness,
and I hope that I can continue my studies.

15:19.458 --> 15:23.458
As Jayce's patron of many years,
I can speak for his character.

15:23.541 --> 15:25.166
I believe that one day,

15:25.250 --> 15:27.500
he will be a great contributor
to our society.

15:27.583 --> 15:29.666
He destroyed a building.

15:29.750 --> 15:33.333
Is this the sort of contribution
we can expect?

15:33.416 --> 15:34.791
[Heimerdinger] If you were a scientist,

15:34.875 --> 15:38.416
you'd know you can't make a prototype
without breaking a few wrenches.

15:39.166 --> 15:42.250
Do you have anything to show
for your work besides an explosion?

15:42.333 --> 15:44.916
Uh, no. It came to nothing.

15:45.000 --> 15:47.625
[Mel] So, you're saying
your study was meaningless?

15:47.708 --> 15:50.583
-It was revolutionary!
-Revolutionary how?

15:50.666 --> 15:54.250
All I see is a boy meddling with things
he doesn't understand.

15:54.333 --> 15:57.041
The Academy seems
to have loosened its standards.

15:57.125 --> 15:59.666
This is a fine line.
If we condone this, what's next?

15:59.750 --> 16:00.958
[Salo] Ridiculous, really.

16:01.041 --> 16:02.916
[Shoola] The Council has more
important matters to deal with.

16:03.000 --> 16:05.041
[Mel] Perhaps we should just finish this…

16:05.125 --> 16:07.833
I was trying to create magic.

16:07.916 --> 16:09.875
[crowd exclaiming]

16:09.958 --> 16:10.958
[crunches]

16:14.000 --> 16:15.000
Magic?

16:15.083 --> 16:17.750
Arcane talents are something
you're born with.

16:17.833 --> 16:20.000
They can't be fabricated.

16:20.083 --> 16:22.041
Actually, I believe it is possible.

16:22.875 --> 16:25.250
Has anyone even tried it before?

16:26.750 --> 16:28.125
[Bolbok clears throat]

16:28.208 --> 16:33.000
The Arcane is the curse of our world.
My race was nearly destroyed by it.

16:33.083 --> 16:37.375
Surely, we, the pioneers of science,
can use it for good.

16:37.458 --> 16:41.333
We're the champions of discovery.
Why fear it when we can master it?

16:41.416 --> 16:42.375
Jayce, enough.

16:42.458 --> 16:46.416
This is the city of progress,
think of the wonders we could create.

16:46.500 --> 16:48.541
-Let me prove--
-[Heimerdinger] Enough!

16:49.666 --> 16:51.875
You don't understand what's at stake.

16:52.916 --> 16:54.375
But how can you?

16:55.041 --> 16:57.541
That's a burden that only I here carry.

16:58.583 --> 16:59.791
Time.

17:01.875 --> 17:05.041
I've seen this power in the wrong hands.

17:05.541 --> 17:11.166
It corrupts, consumes,
lays waste to civilizations.

17:13.375 --> 17:17.458
That cannot happen here, my boy.
It must not.

17:18.375 --> 17:20.333
Heimerdinger is right.

17:20.416 --> 17:23.916
Piltover was founded to escape
the warmongering of mages,

17:24.000 --> 17:26.250
-not cultivate it.
-[Bolbok mutters]

17:26.333 --> 17:30.208
The Ethos is clear.
He must be banished from Piltover.

17:30.291 --> 17:31.125
[gasps]

17:31.208 --> 17:33.166
[crowd muttering]

17:33.250 --> 17:34.500
[Ximena] Please, let me speak!

17:35.083 --> 17:37.208
[footsteps approaching]

17:39.541 --> 17:42.833
As a lower house, my voice
doesn't carry much weight here.

17:42.916 --> 17:46.458
But as a mother,
I have a voice that matters deeply.

17:47.500 --> 17:50.250
My son isn't in his right mind.

17:51.041 --> 17:53.958
His entire life,
he's chased an impossible dream.

17:54.916 --> 17:59.000
What he did was, uh, foolish and unwise.

17:59.833 --> 18:04.208
But he has a good heart.
Please, let him come home.

18:04.291 --> 18:08.666
A crime like this can't be overlooked.
The boy must be punished.

18:08.750 --> 18:12.166
A violation of the Ethos
calls for banishment,

18:12.250 --> 18:16.250
but I can sympathize with a young man's
dream to change the world.

18:16.833 --> 18:20.583
Perhaps in this matter,
a lesser sentence may suffice.

18:20.666 --> 18:24.625
I move that Jayce be summarily expelled
from the Academy

18:24.708 --> 18:27.541
and remanded to the care of his parents.

18:27.625 --> 18:29.375
All those in favor?

18:33.041 --> 18:36.458
[ominous music plays]

18:45.333 --> 18:47.958
[Heimerdinger]
You may take your son home, Mrs. Talis,

18:48.041 --> 18:51.416
but he is to never set foot
on Academy grounds again.

18:51.500 --> 18:54.750
[door whirring]

19:11.208 --> 19:14.333
[disembodied voices]

19:14.416 --> 19:16.458
[approaching footsteps]

19:24.791 --> 19:29.291
First time I've been invited to the Lanes.
It better be worth my time.

19:30.583 --> 19:33.083
Ah, you see, that's your weakness, Marcus.

19:33.166 --> 19:37.333
You carry your chin so high,
you fail to see the opportunity below.

19:37.416 --> 19:38.541
[Marcus] Who are you?

19:39.083 --> 19:41.583
You're looking for four children,

19:41.666 --> 19:44.708
the ones running circles
around Piltover's finest.

19:44.791 --> 19:46.041
[Marcus] What about it?

19:46.708 --> 19:51.000
Don't look so concerned.
I'm about to make your day.

19:52.375 --> 19:55.000
-[thunder rumbling]
-[rain pattering]

20:00.208 --> 20:02.041
[knocks on door]

20:02.125 --> 20:04.416
-[door opens]
-[Ximena] Can I come in?

20:08.291 --> 20:09.458
Hmm.

20:09.958 --> 20:13.833
I still remember the look on your face
when you found these.

20:15.291 --> 20:16.541
[sighs]

20:17.375 --> 20:22.083
Jayce, please. If I hadn't spoken,
you'd be lost to me.

20:23.583 --> 20:25.000
I had to say something.

20:26.000 --> 20:27.833
Magic saved your life.

20:28.375 --> 20:33.916
Yes, but it won't save yours now.
You need to let it go.

20:34.500 --> 20:36.500
I could've convinced the Council.

20:37.000 --> 20:40.708
If my own family won't help me,
I'll find someone who will.

20:41.583 --> 20:44.833
[dramatic music plays]

20:51.875 --> 20:54.041
[Heimerdinger] Oh. That foolish boy.

20:54.125 --> 20:57.250
[Viktor] Yeah, I must admit,
his theory intrigues.

20:57.333 --> 20:59.833
If dangerous ideas
didn't excite the imagination,

20:59.916 --> 21:01.500
we would never wander astray.

21:01.583 --> 21:06.541
Could it work? Could these stones
really invoke magic?

21:06.625 --> 21:08.958
Nonsense. It's far too unstable.

21:09.458 --> 21:11.041
Could you stabilize it?

21:11.125 --> 21:13.291
Me? Why would I?

21:13.375 --> 21:15.166
That only leads to more problems,

21:15.250 --> 21:17.458
and that poor boy
has enough of them already.

21:17.541 --> 21:22.500
There. Come tomorrow morning,
his research will be safely disposed of.

21:23.208 --> 21:24.166
[Heimerdinger] Lock up.

21:25.541 --> 21:30.416
No, no, no. Magic is far too dangerous
in the wrong hands.

21:34.250 --> 21:35.625
[Silco] Will he live?

21:36.625 --> 21:37.875
[Singed] Long enough.

21:38.500 --> 21:41.291
[water gurgles]

21:48.125 --> 21:49.666
Beautiful, aren't they?

21:51.375 --> 21:55.166
Yet, up there on the surface,

21:55.250 --> 21:57.458
no one even knows they exist.

21:58.208 --> 21:59.666
They're monsters.

22:03.208 --> 22:04.958
There's a monster inside all of us.

22:06.750 --> 22:10.583
What? No. No, no! It'll kill me!

22:13.833 --> 22:16.833
I'd like to let you in
on a very important secret

22:16.916 --> 22:19.458
I learned when I was about your age, boy.

22:21.291 --> 22:23.500
You see, power,

22:24.083 --> 22:28.208
real power doesn't come to those
who were born strongest,

22:28.291 --> 22:30.833
or fastest, or smartest.

22:31.875 --> 22:33.416
No.

22:33.500 --> 22:38.916
It comes to those
who will do anything to achieve it.

22:40.833 --> 22:44.458
-It's time to let the monster out.
-[heavy breathing]

22:45.083 --> 22:47.833
[tense music plays]

22:52.791 --> 22:54.916
[panting]

22:57.666 --> 23:00.916
[Deckard grunting]

23:04.125 --> 23:07.666
[growls]

23:08.791 --> 23:11.416
[Deckard screams]

23:20.916 --> 23:23.833
-[rain pattering]
-[mysterious music plays]

23:26.125 --> 23:28.291
[clanking]

23:29.750 --> 23:31.166
[Caitlyn] They won't see you.

23:32.416 --> 23:33.958
Your name's no good now.

23:35.000 --> 23:40.208
My dad says you're a misfit,
and that we can't be friends anymore.

23:41.000 --> 23:42.625
So, why are you out here?

23:43.875 --> 23:46.291
I'm a misfit too, I suppose.

23:47.333 --> 23:48.500
What will you do?

23:50.583 --> 23:53.000
Join the Talis hammer business, I guess.

23:53.083 --> 23:54.708
You can't do that.

23:55.916 --> 23:58.041
No, I can't.

24:00.416 --> 24:03.583
Come inside, Caitlyn. Now.

24:11.666 --> 24:14.250
I'm sorry. I just wanted to explain…

24:14.333 --> 24:15.875
I think you've done enough.

24:17.250 --> 24:19.958
[thunder rumbles]

24:22.916 --> 24:24.833
[Mel] You said this was a robbery.

24:24.916 --> 24:27.375
-Did they take anything dangerous?
-[Grayson] Hard to say.

24:27.458 --> 24:31.250
We don't exactly know what we did find,
let alone what we didn't.

24:31.333 --> 24:34.708
This mention of magic
has the people afraid.

24:34.791 --> 24:37.166
The culprits must be apprehended.

24:37.250 --> 24:39.916
We're doing our best, Councilor.
I assure you.

24:40.000 --> 24:44.041
Your attitude makes me question
if your best is up to the task.

24:44.125 --> 24:45.916
Oh, we'll find them. Don't worry.

24:46.000 --> 24:50.625
We've conducted exhaustive interrogations,
frozen commerce for half the district.

24:50.708 --> 24:52.333
With all due respect, Councilor,

24:52.416 --> 24:55.166
don't you think
we've pushed them hard enough?

24:55.250 --> 24:57.416
Do whatever it takes.

24:57.500 --> 25:00.208
Turn the undercity upside down
if you have to.

25:00.291 --> 25:02.291
Just find them!

25:03.500 --> 25:06.625
[indistinct chatter]

25:14.416 --> 25:16.375
Welcome to The Last Drop.

25:17.000 --> 25:20.541
[enforcers wheeze]

25:24.875 --> 25:27.541
-What can I get you?
-Four sump-rats will do.

25:29.541 --> 25:30.500
Search the place.

25:31.041 --> 25:32.375
[enforcer growls]

25:34.666 --> 25:38.458
While you're wasting your time,
how about a proper drink?

25:38.541 --> 25:40.750
I'll take the strongest shit you got.

25:47.750 --> 25:50.208
[metal clanking]

25:53.291 --> 25:54.625
[wheezes]

25:55.291 --> 25:56.875
[clanking]

25:56.958 --> 25:58.750
[wheezes]

26:01.500 --> 26:03.625
[approaching footsteps]

26:03.708 --> 26:05.750
[raspy breathing]

26:08.125 --> 26:11.541
[creaks]

26:29.333 --> 26:30.958
[enforcer grunts]

26:32.916 --> 26:34.166
[growls]

26:35.250 --> 26:38.458
-[men laughing]
-[sniffs]

26:40.500 --> 26:43.083
[Vander] Mm. You be careful with that.

26:44.750 --> 26:47.750
Nearly forgot.
I ran into an old friend of yours.

26:47.833 --> 26:50.083
[chuckles]
He had some stories.

26:53.708 --> 26:55.416
[grunts]

26:59.875 --> 27:02.458
You weren't always the peacekeeper,
were you?

27:03.041 --> 27:04.125
[grunts]

27:04.208 --> 27:05.458
[sizzles]

27:05.541 --> 27:09.583
Yeah, well,
you can't escape the past. Right?

27:10.583 --> 27:12.958
Be a shame if I had to put them on again.

27:14.000 --> 27:17.625
Cast iron's, well, it's hard to clean.

27:18.375 --> 27:21.375
[tense music plays]

27:28.958 --> 27:30.583
[raspy breathing]

27:41.583 --> 27:44.583
[tense music playing continues]

27:45.458 --> 27:47.625
[creaking]

27:55.166 --> 27:57.041
-[door closes]
-[Powder grunts]

27:57.125 --> 27:58.500
[sighs]

28:01.125 --> 28:02.500
[raspy breathing]

28:10.916 --> 28:13.333
You people down here are all the same,

28:13.416 --> 28:15.916
mistaking arrogance for bravery.

28:16.500 --> 28:19.041
You think you're standing up
for something,

28:19.125 --> 28:20.708
but we all know there is a crime

28:20.791 --> 28:23.666
behind every coin
that passes through this place.

28:26.416 --> 28:30.958
You're just a small man
in a little hole the world forgot to bury.

28:33.166 --> 28:35.250
And I'm gonna bury the lot of you.

28:37.833 --> 28:39.958
[both grunt]

28:40.041 --> 28:40.875
[groans]

28:43.083 --> 28:44.458
[door opens, slams close]

28:47.875 --> 28:50.583
-Are you all okay?
-[Vi grunts]

28:50.666 --> 28:53.083
No, we're not okay.
They almost saw Powder.

28:53.166 --> 28:56.208
-What if they took her?
-No one is taking any of you.

28:56.291 --> 28:59.416
-Never let that happen.
-It's already happening.

28:59.500 --> 29:02.916
You heard him, they won't stop.
We need to fight back.

29:03.000 --> 29:03.958
[clanking]

29:04.916 --> 29:08.000
And if you won't, I will.

29:08.833 --> 29:10.750
[sighs]

29:10.833 --> 29:12.916
I've heard this kind of talk before.

29:14.958 --> 29:17.208
[thunder rumbles]

29:20.458 --> 29:23.166
[fire crackles]

29:26.041 --> 29:28.875
[foreboding music plays]

29:41.375 --> 29:42.458
Why are we here?

29:43.041 --> 29:44.416
[sighs]

29:44.500 --> 29:46.208
You still don't understand.

29:46.291 --> 29:49.625
What I don't understand
is how you can work with them.

29:50.500 --> 29:53.041
We were here. We saw what they did.

29:53.916 --> 29:59.166
I grew up knowing I'm less than them,
that my place is down there.

30:00.041 --> 30:04.250
I want Powder to have more than that,
and I'm willing to fight for it.

30:05.583 --> 30:10.541
So was I. I was angry, just like you.

30:10.625 --> 30:15.375
I led us across this bridge,
thinking things could change.

30:17.125 --> 30:18.333
If I hadn't…

30:19.166 --> 30:22.250
your parents would still be alive.

30:23.750 --> 30:27.666
I know you wanna hurt the topsiders
for what they've done to us.

30:27.750 --> 30:30.041
But who are you willing to lose?

30:30.125 --> 30:32.666
Mylo? Claggor?

30:33.583 --> 30:34.916
Powder?

30:36.375 --> 30:38.958
[thunder rumbles]

30:41.625 --> 30:44.291
Nobody wins in war, Vi.

30:51.625 --> 30:52.625
What are we gonna do?

30:54.125 --> 30:55.583
The Enforcers will come back.

30:57.291 --> 31:02.625
I… I don't know.
I'll, uh, I'll figure it out.

31:05.708 --> 31:08.041
-[bell tolls in distance]
-[indistinct chatter]

31:11.708 --> 31:13.833
[indistinct chatter]

31:14.666 --> 31:17.041
[somber music plays]

31:17.125 --> 31:18.333
[sighs]

31:31.583 --> 31:34.166
[somber music playing continues]

31:53.916 --> 31:55.083
[Viktor] Am I interrupting?

31:55.166 --> 31:56.166
[rocks crumbling]

31:58.958 --> 32:04.125
The hell's your problem? What's that?
Another list with my name on it?

32:04.208 --> 32:08.291
Actually, yes,
but only because you signed your notes.

32:08.375 --> 32:13.250
Every page, I might add.
Eh, a little egotistical, don't you think?

32:13.333 --> 32:15.875
Is that why you came? To insult me?

32:17.208 --> 32:21.875
No, no, I was… I was intrigued
by what you said at the trial.

32:21.958 --> 32:23.708
That makes you the only one.

32:23.791 --> 32:26.208
Yes, well, I wanted
to talk about your work.

32:26.291 --> 32:28.958
This Hextech theory of yours.

32:29.041 --> 32:30.791
It's not a theory.

32:30.875 --> 32:36.291
I saw with my own eyes what magic can do,
the lives it could save.

32:36.375 --> 32:39.250
You've no idea how beautiful it is.

32:40.666 --> 32:44.125
And now it's gone. No one believed me.

32:45.208 --> 32:47.250
Nobody's ever believed in me.

32:48.666 --> 32:50.833
A poor cripple from the undercity.

32:51.916 --> 32:54.708
I was an outsider the moment
I stepped foot in Piltover.

32:55.666 --> 32:59.458
I didn't have the benefits
of a patron or a name.

33:00.416 --> 33:02.208
I simply believed in myself.

33:03.500 --> 33:07.958
Which is why I'm here
because I think you're on to something.

33:08.583 --> 33:11.416
I want to help you complete your research.

33:11.500 --> 33:13.583
No one thinks it can be done.

33:14.625 --> 33:18.666
When you're going to change the world,
don't ask for permission.

33:20.083 --> 33:23.083
[dramatic music plays]

33:33.208 --> 33:34.833
I don't even know your name.

33:36.125 --> 33:37.416
It's Viktor.

33:40.833 --> 33:43.791
-[breathes deeply]
-[door opens]

33:44.916 --> 33:47.791
-Vi, where you been?
-Rumor is the Lanes are gonna fight.

33:54.791 --> 33:56.708
Look, I made them for the Enforcers.

33:56.791 --> 34:00.083
These are smoke bombs,
and those two are full of nails.

34:00.666 --> 34:01.625
[chuckles]

34:01.708 --> 34:04.333
They're gonna work this time, I know it.

34:06.000 --> 34:07.041
Me too.

34:14.833 --> 34:18.875
You know, Powder,
what makes you different makes you strong.

34:19.750 --> 34:21.583
Always remember that, okay?

34:29.291 --> 34:32.916
[Grayson] What the hell were you thinking,
going into The Last Drop?

34:33.000 --> 34:36.916
-Do you have any idea what you've done?
-I was getting results!

34:37.000 --> 34:39.416
-[Marcus] You heard the Council.
-You're a fool.

34:39.500 --> 34:41.791
There is no stopping what happens now.

34:43.166 --> 34:44.208
-[hisses]
-[clanks]

34:47.833 --> 34:49.625
Maybe it's not too late.

34:58.000 --> 35:02.000
["Our Love" playing]

35:15.708 --> 35:20.666
♪ There's a girl in town
And words gone around ♪

35:20.750 --> 35:22.625
♪ She's just fine ♪

35:22.708 --> 35:23.916
[loud thud]

35:24.958 --> 35:31.666
♪ So I don't worry in my head
'Cause I know her heart is tied to mine ♪

35:33.291 --> 35:36.750
♪ Ooh, like some day, I pray ♪

35:36.833 --> 35:39.458
-♪ Our love will always stay ♪
-[man grunts]

35:39.541 --> 35:40.500
[glass shatters]

35:43.000 --> 35:50.000
